# Cursor AI Rules for Digital ID Project

## CRITICAL DEVELOPMENT STANDARDS

### Icons
- **NEVER use emojis** - Always use Font Awesome 6 icons
- Font Awesome is loaded globally in `includes/header.php`
- Use `<i class="fas fa-icon-name"></i>` format
- Browse icons at: https://fontawesome.com/icons

### Language
- **ALWAYS use UK English spelling** - Never American English
- Common corrections:
  - organisation (not organization)
  - synchronisation (not synchronization)
  - colour (not color) - in text content only, CSS properties are fine
  - centre (not center) - in text content only, CSS properties are fine
  - optimise, recognise, authorise, customise, analyse, licence, defence, offence, programme, behaviour, favour, honour, labour, neighbour, realise, specialise, utilise

### Reference Documents
- See `DEVELOPMENT_GUIDELINES.md` for complete standards
- Always check existing code patterns before implementing new features

### Before Committing
- [ ] No emojis used
- [ ] All icons use Font Awesome
- [ ] UK English spelling throughout
- [ ] Code follows existing patterns

